-- allium: 3
-- specs/dispatch/unified_stream_dispatch.allium
--
-- Scope: the Tier-3 post-implementation contract for the server's
-- per-tick dispatch model. Today (Tier-2) the server runs Option A
-- per-stream dispatch — one llama_decode per active stream per tick,
-- as described by PerStreamDispatch in
-- specs/kv-cache/n_stream_layer.allium. Tier 3 of
-- PHASE_NSTREAM_KV_PERF.md REPLACES that loop with one llama_decode
-- per tick whose batch's ne[3] axis indexes the active streams; each
-- stream contributes a uniform number of tokens per the
-- UniformShapePerTick invariant below.
--
-- Why this spec exists: the per-stream dispatch model recovers Bug C
-- absence (each call sees a single-seq batch) but pays a per-stream
-- llama_decode overhead — at NP=8 that's 8 graph submissions, 8
-- update_cache_copies invocations, 8 cudaGraphExecUpdate patches per
-- tick. The TG-NP=8 regression carried over from PHASE_NSTREAM_KV
-- (-6.2 %) traces to this dispatch overhead, not to any kernel cost.
-- Tier 3 collapses the loop to one llama_decode whose batch spans
-- all N active streams; the existing PSKV per-slot kernel already
-- grids over Q->ne[3] as n_seqs
-- (ik_llama.cpp/ggml/src/ggml-cuda/fattn-per-slot-kv-singlewarp-sm75.cu:
-- 363), so the kernel-side change is "pass n_active_streams in
-- ne[3]" rather than "port a new kernel".
--
-- The contracts below describe the POST-TIER-3 state. No
-- implementation in tree satisfies them yet; the RED test at
-- tests/spec/test-unified-stream-dispatch.cpp (P0.B.S4) FAILS on
-- HEAD and PASSES when T3.b + T3.c land.
--
-- Includes:
--   - External entities for the unified-tick objects (UnifiedBatch,
--     StreamSlot, the active-stream set, the tick the dispatch fires
--     against).
--   - Enumerations for the stream's per-tick eligibility state and
--     the per-stream phase the admission logic gates on.
--   - Contracts: UnifiedUbatchInvariant (one llama_decode per tick),
--     UniformShapePerTick (one shape per op per call),
--     AdmissionToUnifiedBatch (which streams enter the unified
--     batch), DispatchSemantics (the replacement of the per-stream
--     loop with one call), RaggedFAComposition (the FA kernel sees
--     ne[3] = n_active_streams), PreservesBugCAbsence (composition
--     argument).
--   - System-wide invariants binding the dispatch-call-count
--     property, the per-tick uniformity property, and the
--     composition with the predecessor specs.
--   - Open questions for the admission policy in mixed-phase ticks
--     and the future ragged-FA relaxation.
--
-- Excludes:
--   - Per-stream KV layout (head_dim/kv_size_per_stream/n_head_kv/
--     n_stream axis order). Owned by
--     specs/kv-cache/n_stream_layer.allium. Tier 3 consumes that
--     layout unchanged; the contracts here describe the dispatch
--     above it.
--   - K/V write CPY view patching. Owned by
--     specs/kv-cache/n_stream_layer.allium (the existing
--     update_cache_copies write-side block at
--     ik_llama.cpp/src/llama.cpp:630-749). Tier 3 inherits the
--     write-side patching unchanged; the K-and-V tensors are shared
--     across all streams and the per-stream stride is the same as
--     today.
--   - K/V read-view per-stream patching at NP > 1 with per-stream
--     dispatch. Owned by
--     specs/kv-cache/per_stream_read_view_patching.allium. Tier 3
--     SUBSUMES that spec's load-bearing claim: under unified
--     dispatch, the read views naturally span ne[3] = n_streams
--     instead of being patched per-decode. The Tier-2 patching code
--     becomes redundant (PHASE_NSTREAM_KV_PERF.md T3.f calls this
--     out for the n_stream==1 guards on build_k_shift / build_defrag
--     / v_trans).
--   - Scheduler-level batch composition rules (prefill vs decode).
--     Owned by specs/scheduler/batch_composition.allium. Tier 3
--     dispatched pure-decode or pure-prefill ticks; Tier 4
--     (chunked-prefill admission) supersedes that mode and allows
--     mixed admission under a per-tick token budget K. The Tier 3
--     unified-stream dispatch (ne[3] = n_active_streams, uniform
--     mul_mat shape) is INDEPENDENT of admission mode — Bug C
--     absence holds structurally regardless of which tokens are
--     in the ubatch.
--   - CUDA-graph cache mechanism. Owned by
--     specs/graphs/cuda_graph_reuse.allium. Tier 3's stable
--     topology (one shape per tick) is strictly better for that
--     spec's TopologyHashLookup; cross-referenced below in
--     RaggedFAComposition's guidance but no contract surface
--     duplicated here.
--   - Ragged FA (per-stream ne[1] mismatch). Tier 3's initial form
--     pins per-stream ne[1] to a single value via
--     UniformShapePerTick. The ragged variant is a future
--     relaxation, called out as OQ-3 below but explicitly NOT a
--     load-bearing contract clause in the initial Tier 3 surface.

-- ============================================================
-- External entities — unified dispatch objects
-- ============================================================

-- The set of streams managed by one llama_context. Sized at
-- start-time from --parallel N (cparams.n_seq_max). Streams that
-- have never been bound to a slot are present in the set but
-- inactive; the Tier-3 unified batch indexes only the active
-- subset. Mirrors the Stream entity in
-- specs/kv-cache/n_stream_layer.allium; redeclared here as external
-- so this spec's contracts are self-contained.
entity StreamSlot {
    stream_id: Integer
    phase: StreamPhase
    has_pending_decode_token: Boolean
    pending_token_count: Integer
}

-- One server tick — the update_slots() iteration that today calls
-- process_batch_tokens once. Mirrors the Tick entity in
-- specs/scheduler/batch_composition.allium; redeclared external for
-- self-containment.
entity Tick {
    index: Integer
}

-- One unified batch assembled for one tick. Replaces the per-stream
-- batch_view at
-- ik_llama.cpp/examples/server/server-context.cpp:4665-4674 (Tier-3
-- T3.b in PHASE_NSTREAM_KV_PERF.md). Carries N active streams' tokens
-- packed into a single ne[3]-axis dimension; the per-stream ne[1]
-- (token count) is uniform across active streams within this batch
-- per UniformShapePerTick.
entity UnifiedBatch {
    tick: Tick
    n_active_streams: Integer
    per_stream_token_count: Integer
    total_token_count: Integer
}

-- One per-stream contribution to the UnifiedBatch. The token list
-- the stream contributed; in the Tier-3 initial form this list has
-- length per_stream_token_count for every active stream. The
-- batch back-reference plus the slice's stream_id together identify
-- the ne[3] index assigned to this slice (per
-- AdmissionOrderPreservesStreamId).
entity UnifiedBatchSlice {
    batch: UnifiedBatch
    stream_id: Integer
    token_count: Integer
    is_prefill: Boolean
    is_decode: Boolean
}

-- One llama_decode invocation observed by the libllama API. The
-- Tier-3 contract is that exactly one of these fires per Tick when
-- any stream contributes, regardless of n_active_streams. Mirrors the
-- existing per-call llama_decode at
-- ik_llama.cpp/examples/server/server-context.cpp:4723; Tier 3 fans
-- out one call instead of looping over runs.
entity LlamaDecodeCall {
    tick: Tick
    batch: UnifiedBatch
}

-- The flash-attention kernel input as seen by the PSKV kernel. The
-- kernel grids over (Q->ne[1], Q->ne[2], Q->ne[3]) per
-- ik_llama.cpp/ggml/src/ggml-cuda/fattn-per-slot-kv-singlewarp-sm75.cu:
-- 361-363. Tier 3 binds Q->ne[3] = batch.n_active_streams; Q->ne[1] =
-- batch.per_stream_token_count.
entity FAKernelInput {
    batch: UnifiedBatch
    q_ne_1: Integer
    q_ne_2: Integer
    q_ne_3: Integer
}

-- One mul_mat / norm / projection op observed within a single
-- llama_decode call. The shape it sees is determined by the unified
-- batch; the UniformShapePerTick contract clauses constrain its
-- input geometry. Modelled as external because the engine does not
-- have a single concrete struct for this; it is the abstract notion
-- of one ggml op invocation.
entity OpInvocation {
    decode_call: LlamaDecodeCall
    op_kind: OpKind
    input_ne_1: Integer
}

-- ============================================================
-- Enumerations
-- ============================================================

-- The per-stream phase at the start of a tick. Mirrors the
-- (state, command) pair from
-- specs/scheduler/batch_composition.allium (idle+load_prompt =
-- load_prompt; processing+none = decode_ready; idle+none =
-- inactive). Collapsed to one enum so the admission contract's
-- predicate is single-axis.
enum StreamPhase {
    inactive                                -- (idle, none): no work pending
    load_prompt                             -- (idle, load_prompt): prefill pending
    decode_ready                            -- (processing, none): has sampled token to decode
    decode_no_token                         -- (processing, none): processing but no pending token this tick
}

-- The kinds of ggml ops the spec quantifies over. Only the
-- shape-bearing ones matter for UniformShapePerTick; op_other is
-- the catch-all for everything else.
enum OpKind {
    op_mul_mat                              -- projection matmuls, logits proj
    op_flash_attn_ext_per_slot_kv           -- PSKV; the production FA path
    op_norm                                 -- RMSNorm
    op_other                                -- everything else (rope, scale, etc.)
}

-- ============================================================
-- Config
-- ============================================================

config {
    -- Maximum streams. Mirrors max_streams in
    -- specs/kv-cache/n_stream_layer.allium and
    -- specs/kv-cache/per_stream_read_view_patching.allium. Pinned
    -- here so the invariants can reference a numeric bound without
    -- cross-spec navigation.
    max_streams: Integer = 8

    -- The minimum per-stream token count the Tier-3 initial form
    -- requires. Decode ticks always run at 1 token per active
    -- stream; the contract pins this value so a future verify-side
    -- multi-token unification (DFlash multi-slot, MTP draft depth)
    -- can override it explicitly rather than implicitly.
    min_per_stream_token_count: Integer = 1
}

-- ============================================================
-- Contracts
-- ============================================================

-- The UnifiedUbatchInvariant — when n_stream > 1 and multiple
-- streams are active, exactly one llama_decode per tick covers all
-- of them. The previous per-stream loop at
-- ik_llama.cpp/examples/server/server-context.cpp:4647-4823 is
-- replaced by a single dispatch; the contract binds the call-count
-- property of the post-Tier-3 implementation.
contract UnifiedUbatchInvariant {
    invoke: (tick: Tick, streams: Set<StreamSlot>) -> LlamaDecodeCall

    @invariant ExactlyOneDecodeCallPerActiveTick
        -- For any tick T where any stream has phase = decode_ready
        -- (i.e. at least one stream has a sampled token ready to
        -- decode), exactly one llama_decode is invoked. The
        -- previous loop's `for (i = 0; i < batch.n_tokens; ...)`
        -- structure dissolves: the assembled batch spans the
        -- active streams along ne[3] and one decode call submits
        -- the whole shape.

    @invariant DecodeCallBatchIndexesActiveStreamsViaNe3
        -- The submitted UnifiedBatch carries
        -- batch.n_active_streams = count of streams with
        -- phase = decode_ready in this tick. That count becomes
        -- the ne[3] dimension of Q, K, V tensors in the FA path
        -- and of the mul_mat inputs in the projection path.

    @invariant NoCallsAtIdleTick
        -- If no stream has phase = decode_ready and no stream has
        -- phase = load_prompt in this tick, no llama_decode fires.
        -- The previous per-stream loop's "if batch.n_tokens == 0
        -- skip" condition is preserved at the unified level.

    @invariant PrefillTickIsSeparate
        -- A stream with phase = load_prompt takes a SEPARATE
        -- llama_decode invocation in its own tick. Decode-ready
        -- streams stall for that tick under
        -- batch_composition.allium's DecodeHoldGate (still in
        -- force; see PreservesBugCAbsence below). The unified
        -- batch contract applies to decode ticks only; prefill
        -- ticks still run one-stream-per-call.

    @guidance
        -- Pending Tier 3: unified-stream dispatch + ragged FA.
        -- RED test in
        -- tests/spec/test-unified-stream-dispatch.cpp will fail on
        -- HEAD. The current dispatch loop at
        -- ik_llama.cpp/examples/server/server-context.cpp:4647-4823
        -- emits one llama_decode per primary-seq_id run; this
        -- contract requires exactly one call regardless of how
        -- many streams contribute.
}

-- The UniformShapePerTick — within one llama_decode, every
-- mul_mat / FA / norm sees one shape per call. The per-stream ne[1]
-- (token count) is the SAME for every active stream in this batch.
-- This is the Q1 composition argument from
-- PHASE_NSTREAM_KV_PERF.md (lines 1911-1915), formalised as a
-- contract: the within-tick GEMM/GEMV decision is consistent because
-- every op sees one shape per call, just as it did under per-stream
-- dispatch — only now the single-call shape includes the n_streams
-- axis at ne[3] rather than being one of N per-stream calls.
contract UniformShapePerTick {
    invoke: (call: LlamaDecodeCall) -> Boolean

    @invariant PerStreamTokenCountIsUniform
        -- For UnifiedBatch b dispatched by call c, every
        -- UnifiedBatchSlice s with s.batch = b has the same
        -- s.token_count. The shared value is
        -- b.per_stream_token_count. Mixed per-stream token counts
        -- within one unified batch are forbidden in the Tier-3
        -- initial form; the ragged variant (OQ-3) would relax this
        -- but is not part of the load-bearing contract surface.

    @invariant EveryOpSeesOneShapePerCall
        -- For OpInvocation o with o.decode_call = c, the op sees a
        -- single shape value for its input_ne_1: there is no
        -- branch within the call that produces o.input_ne_1
        -- differing across active streams. Specifically:
        -- mul_mat for Q/K/V projections, output projection, MLP
        -- FC1/FC2 all see one (head_dim, n_tokens_per_call,
        -- n_streams) shape per call; the GEMM-vs-GEMV dispatcher
        -- branch picks once per op-invocation, not per-stream.

    @invariant FAInputShapeIsBatchScoped
        -- For FAKernelInput fa with fa.batch = b: fa.q_ne_1 =
        -- b.per_stream_token_count; fa.q_ne_3 = b.n_active_streams.
        -- The kernel grids over (ne[1], ne[2], ne[3]) per
        -- fattn-per-slot-kv-singlewarp-sm75.cu:363 and the per-CTA
        -- bind is one (token, head, stream) tuple.

    @invariant NoCrossShapeDispatcherBranchWithinCall
        -- The mmvq / MMQ / MMV dispatcher (the historical Bug C
        -- root cause) selects a kernel template based on the
        -- input's (ne[0], ne[1], dtype) tuple. Under
        -- UnifiedShape, the input has one such tuple per op per
        -- call, so the dispatcher's selection is single-valued.
        -- The contract names this property explicitly because the
        -- Tier-3 transition risks reintroducing cross-shape
        -- dispatch if a future refactor were to per-stream-loop
        -- INSIDE one llama_decode (e.g. for ragged FA). Any such
        -- per-stream looping MUST preserve EveryOpSeesOneShapePerCall.

    @guidance
        -- Pending Tier 3: this contract becomes load-bearing for
        -- Bug C absence under unified dispatch. The previous
        -- per-stream-dispatch model achieved "one shape per call"
        -- by running N calls; Tier 3 achieves the same property
        -- by running one call with one shape spanning N streams.
        -- The composition argument in PreservesBugCAbsence below
        -- closes the loop.
}

-- The AdmissionToUnifiedBatch — which streams enter the decode-tick
-- unified batch. A stream is admitted iff it has at least one
-- decode token ready (phase = decode_ready). Streams in
-- load_prompt take their own prefill tick (preserving
-- batch_composition.allium's BatchCompositionInvariant); streams
-- in decode_no_token wait for their next sampled token.
contract AdmissionToUnifiedBatch {
    invoke: (tick: Tick, streams: Set<StreamSlot>) -> UnifiedBatch

    @invariant AdmissionRequiresDecodeReady
        -- A stream s contributes a UnifiedBatchSlice to this tick's
        -- UnifiedBatch iff s.phase = decode_ready AND
        -- s.has_pending_decode_token. The two clauses are
        -- equivalent at the implementation level (decode_ready
        -- implies has_pending_decode_token) but stated separately
        -- to bind both the lifecycle state AND the readiness
        -- predicate the admission code checks.

    @invariant LoadPromptStreamsNotAdmittedToDecodeTick
        -- A stream s with s.phase = load_prompt is NOT admitted to
        -- a decode-tick unified batch. It runs its own prefill
        -- llama_decode in this tick (one-stream-per-call,
        -- inheriting the existing per-stream dispatch path for
        -- prefill); other decode-ready streams stall this tick
        -- under DecodeHoldGate from batch_composition.allium.

    @invariant InactiveStreamsNeverAdmitted
        -- A stream s with s.phase = inactive is never admitted.
        -- The unified batch's n_active_streams counts only streams
        -- in decode_ready (for decode ticks) or load_prompt (for
        -- prefill ticks).

    @invariant AdmissionOrderPreservesStreamId
        -- The order of UnifiedBatchSlice instances within an
        -- UnifiedBatch is stable: slice for stream s appears at
        -- ne[3] index s.stream_id, regardless of arrival order.
        -- Determinism of the ne[3] index assignment matters for
        -- byte-identity across harness runs (GP3.d, GP3.g in
        -- PHASE_NSTREAM_KV_PERF.md).

    @guidance
        -- Pending Tier 3: the admission predicate lives at
        -- ik_llama.cpp/examples/server/server-context.cpp:4637
        -- onwards (process_batch_tokens). Today the function
        -- iterates by primary seq_id run; Tier 3 replaces the
        -- iteration with a single unified-batch assembly. The RED
        -- test at tests/spec/test-unified-stream-dispatch.cpp
        -- exercises a 2-stream decode-ready tick and asserts
        -- exactly one llama_decode fires (FAIL on HEAD; PASS after
        -- T3.b).
}

-- The DispatchSemantics — the operational replacement of the
-- per-stream loop. Lives at
-- ik_llama.cpp/examples/server/server-context.cpp:4647-4823 (the
-- current per-stream loop with its run detection at 4647-4660 and
-- single llama_decode at 4723). Tier 3 T3.b replaces this with one
-- assembly + one call.
contract DispatchSemantics {
    invoke: (tick: Tick, batch: UnifiedBatch) -> LlamaDecodeCall

    @invariant PerStreamLoopReplacedBySingleCall
        -- The for-loop at server-context.cpp:4647 that iterates
        -- contiguous primary-seq_id runs and emits one
        -- llama_decode per run is REMOVED. In its place: one
        -- assembly step that walks all active streams and emits
        -- one UnifiedBatch, then one llama_decode(ctx,
        -- unified_batch). The runs-by-seq_id splitting logic is no
        -- longer needed because the unified batch is by
        -- construction one-seq-id-per-ne[3]-slot.

    @invariant BatchViewConstructionElidedAtUnifiedSite
        -- The per-stream llama_batch batch_view = { ... } block at
        -- server-context.cpp:4665-4674 (which slices into the
        -- assembled `batch` per run) is replaced by the unified
        -- batch assembly. The unified llama_batch carries the
        -- token / pos / n_seq_id / seq_id / logits arrays directly,
        -- with ne[3]-axis indexing the per-stream segments by
        -- offset within those arrays.

    @invariant ContinueOnFailurePathPreserved
        -- The error-recovery semantics (KV-full retry with halved
        -- n_batch at server-context.cpp:4789-4802; slot release on
        -- ret < 0 at 4744-4787) are preserved at the unified
        -- level. A single llama_decode failure releases all
        -- contributing slots (not just one stream's), because the
        -- failure mode under unified dispatch is whole-batch.

    @invariant TraceEmissionAdaptedToUnifiedShape
        -- The NDJSON TickDispatch event emitted at
        -- server-context.cpp:4687-4712 still fires per dispatch,
        -- but with prefill_slots / decode_slots /
        -- loading_prompt_set computed from the unified batch's
        -- slice list rather than from one run's seq_ids. The
        -- BatchComposition.tla / StreamIsolation.tla validators
        -- continue to receive one record per llama_decode.

    @guidance
        -- The Tier-3 implementation may want to keep the inner
        -- loop body's pre-existing per-slot work (mtp_warmup,
        -- checkpoint save, the per-slot post-decode bookkeeping at
        -- server-context.cpp:4831 onwards). That work fans out
        -- naturally over the unified batch's slice list; it does
        -- NOT re-introduce a per-stream llama_decode. The contract
        -- binds the llama_decode call count to 1 per decode tick,
        -- not the per-slot bookkeeping count.
}

-- The RaggedFAComposition — the FA kernel's per-tick input shape.
-- The kernel sees a batch with ne[3] = n_active_streams; ne[1] =
-- per_stream_token_count. In the Tier-3 initial form, per-stream
-- ne[1] is uniform (UniformShapePerTick). If ragged FA lands later,
-- the contract relaxes to allow per-stream ne[1] mismatch under an
-- explicit ragged-mode dispatcher; document the ragged variant as a
-- future relaxation (OQ-3), not as the initial contract.
contract RaggedFAComposition {
    invoke: (input: FAKernelInput) -> Boolean

    @invariant Ne3EqualsNActiveStreams
        -- For the unified-tick FA invocation,
        -- input.q_ne_3 = input.batch.n_active_streams. The PSKV
        -- kernel grids over (ne[1], ne[2], ne[3]) per
        -- fattn-per-slot-kv-singlewarp-sm75.cu:363; the per-CTA
        -- bind of (token, head, stream) means each CTA reads
        -- exactly one stream's K/V slab via the ne[3]-axis
        -- stride. No cross-stream data crosses any CTA boundary.

    @invariant Ne1EqualsPerStreamTokenCount
        -- For the unified-tick FA invocation,
        -- input.q_ne_1 = input.batch.per_stream_token_count. Under
        -- UniformShapePerTick this is one value across the batch;
        -- the FA kernel sees a uniform per-stream token axis.

    @invariant KVStreamStrideIsParentNb3
        -- The K and V tensors' ne[3] equals the cache's n_stream;
        -- the per-stream stride is parent.nb[3] (the existing
        -- 4D layout from specs/kv-cache/n_stream_layer.allium).
        -- The kernel reads K, V via the ne[3]-axis stride; under
        -- unified dispatch the read paths span n_active_streams
        -- slabs in one launch, rather than one slab per launch.

    @invariant PerRowKBoundConsumedPerStream
        -- The per_row_k_bound tensor (dst->src[5] per
        -- fattn-per-slot-kv-singlewarp-sm75.cu:334) is sized
        -- [n_tokens] with one entry per token-in-batch. Under
        -- unified dispatch it carries n_active_streams *
        -- per_stream_token_count entries; the kernel indexes it
        -- via the linear token position computed from
        -- (ne[1], ne[3]) coordinates. Plumbed today but a no-op
        -- for correctness (the mask handles bound enforcement per
        -- the PSKV P2 closure); the contract names the shape for
        -- the ragged variant's future use.

    @guidance
        -- Pending Tier 3: the FA kernel input today has ne[3] = 1
        -- under per-stream dispatch (one stream per call). The
        -- Tier-3 implementation passes n_active_streams in ne[3];
        -- no kernel changes are needed for this transition because
        -- the kernel already grids over ne[3]. The
        -- RaggedFAComposition contract names what the kernel
        -- consumes; it does not assert any kernel-side
        -- modification. Cross-references the PSKV per-slot kernel
        -- closure in
        -- ~/.claude/projects/-home-llm-yarn-agentic/memory/project_fattn_per_slot_kv_p2_landed_kernel_only.md.
        -- RED test in tests/spec/test-unified-stream-dispatch.cpp
        -- will fail on HEAD because no current call site produces
        -- ne[3] > 1 for FA input (per-stream dispatch keeps it
        -- at 1).
}

-- The PreservesBugCAbsence — the composition argument: under
-- Tier-3 unified dispatch, the historical Bug C closure mechanism
-- is preserved by construction. Bug C was "mixed shape WITHIN a
-- tick"; unified dispatch achieves single-shape-per-tick differently
-- from per-stream dispatch (one call with one shape including the
-- n_streams axis at ne[3]) but achieves the same load-bearing
-- property. Cross-references n_stream_layer.allium's StreamPartition
-- and per_stream_read_view_patching.allium's PerStreamReadIsolation
-- (under unified dispatch the read views span ne[3]=n_streams
-- naturally, so the Tier-2 patching becomes redundant).
contract PreservesBugCAbsence {
    invoke: (call: LlamaDecodeCall) -> Boolean

    @invariant UniformShapeArgumentClosesBugC
        -- Bug C's root cause was the mul_mat GEMV-vs-GEMM
        -- dispatcher selecting different reductions for
        -- different shapes within one tick. Under
        -- UniformShapePerTick.EveryOpSeesOneShapePerCall, each
        -- mul_mat invocation sees ONE shape per call, so the
        -- dispatcher branch is single-valued. The Bug C failure
        -- geometry cannot form because there is no within-tick
        -- shape transition for the dispatcher to branch across.

    @invariant StreamPartitionComposesWithUnifiedDispatch
        -- StreamPartition from
        -- specs/kv-cache/n_stream_layer.allium states that each
        -- stream's KV cells live in a well-defined slice of the
        -- underlying tensor. Under unified dispatch, the per-call
        -- K/V tensor is the SAME shared tensor (ne[3]=n_stream);
        -- each ne[3]-axis CTA reads exactly one stream's slice.
        -- The partition is preserved because the kernel's per-CTA
        -- bind selects exactly stream s when CTA z-coordinate = s.

    @invariant PerStreamReadIsolationLiftedToNe3Axis
        -- PerStreamReadIsolation from
        -- specs/kv-cache/per_stream_read_view_patching.allium
        -- states reads bound for stream s only access cells in
        -- stream s's slice. Under unified dispatch, the read view
        -- spans ALL streams (ne[3] = n_stream) and the per-stream
        -- isolation moves from "per-call data pointer offset" to
        -- "per-CTA ne[3]-axis stride". The kernel reads N
        -- disjoint slabs in one launch; cross-stream data crosses
        -- no CTA boundary. The Tier-2 per-call read-view patching
        -- becomes redundant; the underlying isolation property is
        -- stronger under Tier 3 (compile-time stride vs runtime
        -- pointer patch).

    @invariant DispatchOrderAndDeterminismPreserved
        -- Under per-stream dispatch, byte-identity across harness
        -- runs required a stable per-tick dispatch order. Under
        -- unified dispatch, byte-identity requires
        -- AdmissionOrderPreservesStreamId (above): the ne[3]
        -- index for stream s is fixed at s.stream_id, so the
        -- kernel's per-CTA assignment is deterministic across
        -- runs. GP3.d / GP3.g in PHASE_NSTREAM_KV_PERF.md bind
        -- this empirically.

    @invariant BatchCompositionInvariantHoldsAtUnifiedTick
        -- BatchCompositionInvariant from
        -- specs/scheduler/batch_composition.allium (redefined at
        -- Tier 4) states every llama_decode batch satisfies the
        -- chunked-prefill admission shape: tokens.count <= K
        -- AND per-token flag exclusivity. Tier 3 unified
        -- dispatch preserves this regardless of which tokens
        -- are admitted — the ne[3] = n_active_streams structure
        -- and per-stream slab kernel inputs do not depend on
        -- whether each stream contributes prefill or decode
        -- tokens this tick.

    @guidance
        -- Pending Tier 3: this contract is the load-bearing
        -- argument that dropping per-stream dispatch is safe.
        -- Verification: GP3.f (r5-probe-c4.sh ITERS=20 = 0/20)
        -- continues PASS after T3.b lands. The structural Bug C
        -- absence under Tier-2 was scheduler+layout-level; under
        -- Tier-3 it is kernel-input-shape-level — both achieve
        -- the same observable property.
}

-- ============================================================
-- Invariants — system-wide
-- ============================================================

-- The decode-call-count property lifted to a system-wide claim.
-- For any tick, the number of llama_decode invocations equals 1 if
-- any decode-ready stream is admitted, else 0 (or 1 if a prefill
-- stream takes its own tick — covered by PrefillTickIsSeparate).
-- Lifts UnifiedUbatchInvariant.ExactlyOneDecodeCallPerActiveTick.
invariant DecodeCallCountPerTickBounded {
    for tick in Ticks:
        DecodeCallsAt(tick).count <= 1
}

-- The per-tick uniformity property lifted to a system-wide claim.
-- For any tick's UnifiedBatch, every UnifiedBatchSlice has the same
-- token_count. Lifts UniformShapePerTick.PerStreamTokenCountIsUniform.
invariant PerTickUniformShape {
    for batch in UnifiedBatches:
        let slices = SlicesOf(batch)
        slices.all(s => s.token_count = batch.per_stream_token_count)
}

-- The unified-batch admission-mode property. Under Tier 3 this was
-- a pure/pure disjunction (pure-decode or pure-prefill); Tier 4
-- supersedes it with the chunked-prefill admission shape from
-- batch_composition.allium's redefined BatchCompositionInvariant.
-- The per-slice flag exclusivity stays: any individual slice is
-- either decode or prefill, never both. The whole-batch
-- pure/pure constraint does NOT hold under Tier 4 — a single
-- unified batch may contain decode slices and prefill slices.
invariant UnifiedBatchSliceFlagExclusivity {
    for batch in UnifiedBatches:
        let slices = SlicesOf(batch)
        slices.all(s => not (s.is_decode and s.is_prefill))
}

-- The ne[3]-axis identity property. For any unified-tick FA
-- invocation, the kernel's ne[3] equals the batch's
-- n_active_streams. Lifts RaggedFAComposition.Ne3EqualsNActiveStreams.
invariant FANe3EqualsActiveStreamsSystemWide {
    for input in FAKernelInputs:
        input.q_ne_3 = input.batch.n_active_streams
}

-- The admission-determinism property. For any UnifiedBatch, the
-- ne[3] index assigned to each contributing stream equals the
-- stream's stream_id. Lifts
-- AdmissionToUnifiedBatch.AdmissionOrderPreservesStreamId; binding
-- for byte-identity across harness runs.
invariant Ne3IndexEqualsStreamId {
    for slice in UnifiedBatchSlices:
        Ne3IndexFor(slice) = slice.stream_id
}

-- The Bug-C-absence composition lifted to a system-wide claim. For
-- every decode-tick LlamaDecodeCall, the within-call op shapes are
-- single-valued per op (no cross-shape branching) AND the per-CTA
-- KV access is stream-local (StreamPartition holds at the kernel
-- input layer). The conjunction is the Tier-3 structural Bug C
-- absence.
invariant BugCAbsenceUnderUnifiedDispatch {
    for call in LlamaDecodeCalls:
        for op in OpsInvokedDuring(call):
            SingleInputShape(op)
                and KernelInputIsStreamLocal(op, call.batch)
}

-- The graph-cache-friendliness property. Under unified dispatch the
-- per-tick topology is stable (one shape per tick across active
-- streams), so cuda_graph_reuse.allium's TopologyHashLookup hits
-- the same cache entry across consecutive decode ticks at the same
-- n_active_streams. Cross-references that spec's
-- LookupHitReturnsExistingEntry.
invariant StableTopologyAcrossDecodeTicks {
    for t1 in DecodeTicks:
        for t2 in DecodeTicks:
            (t1 != t2
             and NActiveStreams(t1) = NActiveStreams(t2)
             and PerStreamTokenCount(t1) = PerStreamTokenCount(t2))
                implies TopologyHashAt(t1) = TopologyHashAt(t2)
}

-- ============================================================
-- Open Questions
-- ============================================================

-- OQ-1: mixed-phase ticks. A tick where some streams are
--   decode_ready and others are load_prompt forces a choice:
--   (a) prefill-priority — run the prefill tick alone, decode-ready
--       streams stall under DecodeHoldGate (today's behaviour);
--   (b) decode-priority — run the unified decode tick, prefill
--       streams stall;
--   (c) split — run two ticks back-to-back within one update_slots
--       iteration. The contracts above describe (a) as the
--       Tier-3 initial form (PreservesBugCAbsence relies on it).
--       Resolve at T3.b: the implementation MAY choose differently
--       once benchmark gates GP3.i / GP3.j land.
--
-- OQ-2: per_stream_token_count > 1 for decode ticks. The Tier-3
--   initial form uses min_per_stream_token_count = 1; each stream
--   contributes one sampled token per tick. DFlash multi-slot
--   verify and MTP draft depth produce N tokens per stream per
--   tick; the existing dispatch model already handles these by
--   running one llama_decode per stream per tick at ne[1]>1.
--   Tier 3's unified form must compose with these — per the Q3
--   composition argument in PHASE_NSTREAM_KV_PERF.md, the DFlash
--   draft-side is already batched (Phase 5); Tier 3 unifies the
--   verify side. Token counts across streams at ne[1]>1 may differ
--   per stream in principle (mixed-depth speculation), but the
--   initial contract pins per_stream_token_count to be uniform.
--   The asymmetric case is OQ-3.
--
-- OQ-3: ragged FA — per-stream ne[1] mismatch. The PSKV kernel
--   today grids over (ne[1], ne[2], ne[3]) and binds one CTA per
--   (token, head, stream); per-stream ne[1] mismatch would require
--   either padding the shorter streams (waste) or a ragged-mode
--   dispatcher (per-stream effective n_tokens via per_row_k_bound
--   and a per-stream mask). Tier 3's initial form pins
--   PerStreamTokenCountIsUniform; the ragged variant is a future
--   relaxation, not part of the initial contract surface.
--   Resolve when DFlash mixed-depth speculation or asymmetric MTP
--   draft chains land (no current workload demands it).
--
-- OQ-4: prefill tick under unified dispatch — does Tier 3 also
--   unify prefill batches across streams (when multiple streams
--   are in load_prompt simultaneously)? The contracts above pin
--   prefill-as-separate-tick AND one-prefill-stream-per-tick (via
--   PrefillSerialisationGate inherited from
--   batch_composition.allium). If a future platform's mul_mat
--   handles cross-shape prefill cheaply, Tier 3 could also unify
--   prefill across streams; today the gate stays in force as a
--   perf choice. Resolve at GP3.c benchmark.
--
-- OQ-5: cuda_graph cache capacity under Tier 3. With the bailout
--   dropped at Tier 2 and dispatch unified at Tier 3, the cache
--   holds one entry per (n_active_streams, per_stream_token_count,
--   n_kv_bucket) tuple. At n_active_streams ∈ [1, 8],
--   per_stream_token_count ∈ {1, 5} (decode + DFlash verify), and
--   n_kv buckets bucketed to multiples of 64 by
--   ik_llama.cpp/src/llama.cpp:621, the cache holds well below
--   GGML_CUDA_GRAPH_MAX = 128 entries. Verify at GP3.j: instrument
--   ggml_cuda_get_graph_cache to count evictions over a 1000-decode
--   steady-state run.
--
-- OQ-6: MTP fused × Tier 3 chain-residual D2D fast-path. Composition
--   of this spec with [[mtp_fused_x_n_stream]]. At HEAD, MTP's
--   chain_residual buffer (one tensor per fused step, allocated as
--   ggml_tensor_2d [n_embd, 1] in src/llama.cpp:6088-6095) is
--   structurally single-stream — multi-slot batched dispatch
--   STRUCTURALLY SKIPS the arm at
--   examples/server/server-context.cpp:3427-3430, falling back to
--   the host-bounce path (D→H read of embeddings_ith → H→D
--   set_draft_input_hidden_state). Closure recorded in
--   [[mtp_fused_x_n_stream]] as MTPFusedAtN_StreamLessThan2Or1.
--
--   Under Tier 3 unified dispatch, MTP rides on top of the unified
--   batch (UnifiedUbatchInvariant). The chain_residual tensor would
--   then need an ne[3] axis — [n_embd, 1, 1, n_stream] — for the
--   D2D fast-path to compose with unified dispatch. Without that,
--   MTP at Tier 3 multi-slot falls through to host-bounce on every
--   draft cycle. Direct copy cost is ~10-25 µs per cycle for n_embd
--   = 5120; the larger cost is the implicit llama_synchronize
--   barrier the host-bounce introduces (tens to low-hundreds of µs
--   of GPU idle per cycle, depending on pipeline depth).
--
--   At np=8, ~24 cycles/sec → ~600 µs/sec direct + ~5 ms/sec
--   pipeline → up to ~0.5 % of wall time recoverable.
--
--   Resolution: not part of the Tier 3 initial-form contract. The
--   asymmetric case (MTPChainResidualPerStream extension) is
--   tracked in [[mtp_fused_x_n_stream]] and lands separately, IF
--   AND ONLY IF (a) MTP becomes the production multi-slot decode
--   path AND (b) the ~0.5 % recoverable matters relative to the
--   prevailing perf target. Bind at GP3.k: profile MTP fused-cycle
--   wall time at np=8 once Tier 3 lands; if MTP draft-cycle host
--   bounce shows up above the noise floor in nsys traces, open the
--   per-stream chain extension as its own workstream.
--
--   The Tier-3 dispatch contracts above do NOT depend on this OQ
--   resolving either way — UnifiedUbatchInvariant and
--   UniformShapePerTick are independent of MTP arming. This OQ
--   exists to ensure the perf interaction is not lost when MTP
--   composition under Tier 3 is implemented.

